Class VectorQuery

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jeo.vector.VectorQuery

      • adjustCount

        public long adjustCount(long count)
        Adjusts a raw count based on limit and offset of the query.

        The adjusted count is equivalent to: 

         min(max(0, count-offset), limit)

        Returns:
        The adjusted count.

      • missingProperties

        public Set<String> missingProperties(Schema schema)
        Compute missing properties based on the provided schema and the current filter. This allows a format to defer to CQL filtering instead of using native (SQL for example) encoding that may result in errors or invalid results.
        Parameters:
        schema - non-null schema to evaluate the filter against
        Returns:
        non-null Set of any missing properties
